# my-remix-app

> AGENTS.md: instructions for AI coding agents working on this project.
> Human contributors: see README.md.

## Stack

- React 18.3.0
- Node.js
- Remix 2.10.0

## Commands

- `npm run dev`: `remix vite:dev`
- `npm run build`: `remix vite:build`
- `npm run start`: `remix-serve ./build/server/index.js`

## Conventions

- Function components and hooks only.
- Lift state to the lowest common ancestor. Co-locate state with the component that owns it.
- ES modules (`"type": "module"`) with explicit `.js` extensions on imports.
- Use native fetch where available. Reserve axios for interceptor-heavy flows.
- Data via `loader` (GET-like) and `action` (form submissions). Both server-only.
- Nested routing: parents render `<Outlet />`, children compose in. Loaders run in parallel.
- Resource routes (no default export) become API endpoints returning `Response`.

## What to avoid

- Class components in new code.
- Derived state in `useState` when it can be computed during render.
- Mixing CommonJS and ESM in the same package.
- Fetching in components. Move to `loader`; return via `useLoaderData()`.

